# MEDICAL CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: medical
scope: medical.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of medical in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Medical is the bounded health-state structure
through which condition,
assessment,
intervention,
recovery,
restriction,
and clinical history
become meaningful.

## architectural_position
Medical sits between:
- life continuity
- body/condition state
- intervention and care
- work/family/housing consequence
- historical health trace

## required_behavior
- medical context must remain explicit
- assessment/intervention basis must remain explicit
- current and historical medical states must remain distinguishable
- restriction and recovery meaning must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- assessment does not imply unrestricted disclosure
- intervention does not overwrite historical trace
- ambiguous medical scope fails closed

## state_model
The medical domain distinguishes:
- observed condition
- assessed condition
- active intervention
- restricted condition
- recovery state
- historical medical state

## review_checklist
- medical context is explicit
- intervention basis is explicit
- recovery/restriction meaning is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
